## ===========================
##  REGRESSO BINOMIAL ROBUSTA
## ===========================

expit = function(eta) 1/(1+exp(-eta))

set.seed(2025)

## ---------------------------
## Exemplo nico (com rudo)
## ---------------------------
n = 200
m = rep(10, n)
x = runif(n, -2, 2)

alpha = -0.5
beta  =  1.2
theta = c(alpha, beta)

mu = expit(theta[1] + theta[2]*x)
y  = rbinom(n, size=m, prob=mu)

## contaminao (alavanca x e rtulos 0/m)
aux = sample(which(x < 0.5), round(0.10*n))
x[aux] = x[aux] + 3
y[aux] = ifelse(runif(length(aux)) < 0.5, 0, m[aux])

plot(y ~ x, col=ifelse(1:n %in% aux, "tomato", "black"), main="Dados (vermelho = perturbado)")

## MLE (referncia)
fit0 = glm(cbind(y, m - y) ~ x, family=binomial())
theta.hat0 = coef(fit0)

## -------- mtodo robusto (IQR + exp(-|c|)) --------
## p como na lousa
p = 1.5

## Equaes de estimao empilhadas
L = function(theta){
  eta = theta[1] + theta[2]*x
  mu  = expit(eta)
  r   = (y - m*mu)                         # resduo "cru" estilo Poisson da aula
  cut = p * IQR(r)
  c_p = ifelse(abs(r) > cut, exp(-abs(r)), 1)  # atenuao
  cbind( c_p*(y - m*mu),
         c_p* x*(y - m*mu) )
}

## Norma^2 das equaes (para o optim), igual ao LL do prof
LL = function(theta){
  u = colSums(L(theta))
  sum(u^2)
}

## Sandwich no estilo da lousa (B e V)
B = function(theta){
  U = L(theta)
  t(U) %*% U / n
}
V = function(theta){
  eps = 1e-6
  U0  = colSums(L(theta))
  J   = matrix(NA_real_, 2, 2)
  for(j in 1:2){
    th = theta
    th[j] = th[j] + eps
    Uj = colSums(L(th))
    J[, j] = (Uj - U0)/eps
  }
  solve(J) %*% B(theta) %*% t(solve(J))
}

## inicializa em MLE e otimiza
fit1 = optim(LL, par=theta.hat0, control=list(reltol=1e-12))
theta.hat1 = fit1$par
V.hat = V(theta.hat1)

## padronizao com autovetores (mesmo teatrinho V_0.5 e W1)
E = eigen(V.hat)
V_0.5 = E$vectors %*% diag(1/sqrt(E$values)) %*% t(E$vectors)
W1 = sqrt(n) * V_0.5 %*% (theta.hat1 - theta)

par(mfrow=c(1,2))
## curva MLE vs Robusta
xs = seq(min(x), max(x), length.out=200)
lines(xs, expit(theta.hat0[1] + theta.hat0[2]*xs), lwd=2, col="black")
lines(xs, expit(theta.hat1[1] + theta.hat1[2]*xs), lwd=2, col="tomato")
legend("topleft", c("MLE","Robusto (IQR+exp(-|c|))"), col=c("black","tomato"), lwd=2, bty="n")

## marca quem foi atenuado pelo corte atual em vermelho
eta.r = theta.hat1[1] + theta.hat1[2]*x
r.now = (y - m*expit(eta.r))
cut.now = p * IQR(r.now)
plot(y ~ x, col=ifelse(abs(r.now) > cut.now, "tomato", "black"),
     main="Observaes atenuadas em vermelho")

theta       ## verdadeiro
theta.hat0  ## MLE
theta.hat1  ## Robusto
W1          ## vetor padronizado

## ---------------------------
##   Monte Carlo
## ---------------------------
mc_binom_iqrexp = function(R=500, n=200, contam=0.10, p=1.5){
  out = matrix(NA_real_, R, 4)
  colnames(out) = c("b0_mle","b1_mle","b0_rob","b1_rob")
  m = rep(10, n)
  for(t in 1:R){
    x = runif(n, -2, 2)
    mu = expit(theta[1] + theta[2]*x)
    y  = rbinom(n, size=m, prob=mu)
    ## contamina igual ao exemplo
    aux = sample(which(x < 0.5), round(contam*n))
    x[aux] = x[aux] + 3
    y[aux] = ifelse(runif(length(aux)) < 0.5, 0, m[aux])

    ## MLE
    b_mle = coef(glm(cbind(y, m - y) ~ x, family=binomial()))

    ## robusto: mesmo L/LL com p-IQR e exp(-|c|)
    L = function(th){
      eta = th[1] + th[2]*x
      mu  = expit(eta)
      r   = y - m*mu
      c   = p * IQR(r)
      exc = pmax(0, abs(r) - c)
      w   = exp(-exc)
      cbind( w*(y - m*mu),
             w*x*(y - m*mu) )
    }
    LL = function(th){ u = colSums(L(th)); sum(u^2) }

    b_rob = try(optim(LL, par=b_mle, control=list(reltol=1e-12))$par, silent=TRUE)
    if(inherits(b_rob, "try-error")) next
    out[t,] = c(b_mle[1], b_mle[2], b_rob[1], b_rob[2])
  }
  out
}

set.seed(99)
res = mc_binom_iqrexp(R=500, n=200, contam=0.15, p=1.5)

mc_binom_iqrexp = function(R=500, n=200, contam=0.10, p=1.5){
  out = matrix(NA_real_, R, 4)
  colnames(out) = c("b0_mle","b1_mle","b0_rob","b1_rob")
  theta = c(-0.5, 1.2)
  m = rep(10, n)
  for(t in 1:R){
    x = runif(n, -2, 2)
    mu = expit(theta[1] + theta[2]*x)
    y  = rbinom(n, size=m, prob=mu)

    ## contaminao
    aux = sample(which(x < 0.5), round(contam*n))
    x[aux] = x[aux] + 3
    y[aux] = ifelse(runif(length(aux)) < 0.5, 0, m[aux])

    ## MLE
    b_mle = coef(glm(cbind(y, m - y) ~ x, family=binomial()))

    ## robusto
    L = function(th){
      eta = th[1] + th[2]*x
      mu  = expit(eta)
      r   = y - m*mu
      c   = p * IQR(r)
      exc = pmax(0, abs(r) - c)
      w   = exp(-exc)
      cbind( w*(y - m*mu),
             w*x*(y - m*mu) )
    }
    LL = function(th){ u = colSums(L(th)); sum(u^2) }
    b_rob = try(optim(LL, par=b_mle, control=list(reltol=1e-12))$par,
                silent=TRUE)
    if(inherits(b_rob, "try-error")) next
    out[t,] = c(b_mle[1], b_mle[2], b_rob[1], b_rob[2])
  }
  out
}

set.seed(99)
res = mc_binom_iqrexp(R=500, n=200, contam=0.10, p=1.5)

mc_binom_iqrexp = function(R=500, n=200, contam=0.10, p=1.5){
  out = matrix(NA_real_, R, 4)
  colnames(out) = c("b0_mle","b1_mle","b0_rob","b1_rob")
  theta = c(-0.5, 1.2)
  m = rep(10, n)

  for(t in 1:R){
    x = runif(n, -2, 2)
    mu = expit(theta[1] + theta[2]*x)
    y  = rbinom(n, size=m, prob=mu)

    ## contaminao idntica ao exemplo
    aux = sample(which(x < 0.5), round(contam*n))
    x[aux] = x[aux] + 3
    y[aux] = ifelse(runif(length(aux)) < 0.5, 0, m[aux])

    ## MLE
    b_mle = coef(glm(cbind(y, m - y) ~ x, family=binomial()))

    ## Robusto
    L = function(th){
      eta = th[1] + th[2]*x
      mu  = expit(eta)
      r   = y - m*mu
      # r  <- (y - m*mu) / sqrt(pmax(1e-8, m*mu*(1-mu)))   # Pearson
      c   = p * IQR(r)
      exc = pmax(0, abs(r) - c)
      w   = exp(-exc)
      cbind( w*(y - m*mu),
             w*x*(y - m*mu) )
    }
    LL = function(th){ u = colSums(L(th)); sum(u^2) }

    b_rob = try(optim(LL, par=b_mle, control=list(reltol=1e-12))$par,
                silent=TRUE)
    if(inherits(b_rob, "try-error")) next

    out[t,] = c(b_mle[1], b_mle[2], b_rob[1], b_rob[2])
  }
  out
}

plot_hist <- function(z, true, titulo){
  hist(z, prob = TRUE, col = "grey70", border = "white", main = titulo, xlab = "")
  ## curva normal ajustada aos MC
  curve(dnorm(x, mean = mean(z, na.rm=TRUE), sd = sd(z, na.rm=TRUE)),
        add = TRUE, col = "tomato", lwd = 2)
  ## valor verdadeiro (linha tracejada)
  abline(v = true, lty = 2, lwd = 2, col = "steelblue")
  ## mdia Monte Carlo (opcional)
  abline(v = mean(z, na.rm=TRUE), lty = 1, lwd = 1.2, col = "grey30")
  legend("topright",
         c("Normal ajustada", "Valor verdadeiro", "Mdia MC"),
         col = c("tomato", "steelblue", "grey30"),
         lty = c(1, 2, 1), lwd = c(2, 2, 1.2), bty = "n", cex = 0.9)
}

## ==========================================================
##  Binomial robusto (IQR + exp(-(|r|-c)_+)) com contaminao
##  adversria p/ mostrar vis no MLE e robustez no proposto
## ==========================================================

expit = function(eta) 1/(1+exp(-eta))
set.seed(2025)

## --------------------------
## Exemplo nico (adversrio)
## --------------------------
n = 220
m = rep(10, n)
x = runif(n, -2, 2)

theta = c(-0.5, 1.2)
mu = expit(theta[1] + theta[2]*x)
y  = rbinom(n, size=m, prob=mu)

## contaminao adversria: pegue os MAIORES x (alta alavancagem),
## force y=0 (contrariando beta1>0) e empurre x pra direita
contam = 0.18
delta_x = 6
k = round(contam*n)
idx = order(x, decreasing=TRUE)[1:k]
y[idx] = 0
x[idx] = x[idx] + delta_x

## MLE
fit0 = glm(cbind(y, m-y) ~ x, family=binomial())
theta.hat0 = coef(fit0)

## Robusto
p = 1.4
L = function(th){
  eta = th[1] + th[2]*x
  mu  = expit(eta)
  r   = y - m*mu
  c   = p * IQR(r)
  w   = exp(-pmax(0, abs(r) - c))
  cbind( w*(y - m*mu),
         w*x*(y - m*mu) )
}
LL = function(th){ u = colSums(L(th)); sum(u^2) }

B = function(th){ U = L(th); t(U) %*% U / n }
V = function(th){
  eps = 1e-6; U0 = colSums(L(th)); J = matrix(NA_real_,2,2)
  for(j in 1:2){ thj = th; thj[j] = thj[j]+eps; Uj = colSums(L(thj)); J[,j]=(Uj-U0)/eps }
  solve(J) %*% B(th) %*% t(solve(J))
}

fit1 = optim(LL, par=theta.hat0, control=list(reltol=1e-12))
theta.hat1 = fit1$par
V.hat = V(theta.hat1)

## plots do exemplo
par(mfrow=c(1,2))
plot(y/m ~ x, pch=20, col=ifelse(1:n %in% idx, "tomato", "grey40"),
     main="Curvas (vermelho = contaminado)")
xs = seq(min(x), max(x), length=200)
lines(xs, expit(theta.hat0[1] + theta.hat0[2]*xs), lwd=2, col="black")
lines(xs, expit(theta.hat1[1] + theta.hat1[2]*xs), lwd=2, col="tomato")
legend("topleft", c("MLE","Robusto"), col=c("black","tomato"), lwd=2, bty="n")

cut.now = p * IQR(r.now)
plot(y ~ x, col=ifelse(abs(r.now) > cut.now, "tomato", "black"),
     main="Atenuados pelo corte (IQR)", pch=20)

theta      ;  theta.hat0   ;  theta.hat1

## --------------------------
##  Monte Carlo adversrio
## --------------------------
mc_binom_advers = function(R=400, n=220, contam=0.18, delta_x=6, p=1.4){
  out = matrix(NA_real_, R, 4)
  colnames(out) = c("b0_mle","b1_mle","b0_rob","b1_rob")
  theta = c(-0.5, 1.2)
  m = rep(10, n)
  for(t in 1:R){
    x = runif(n, -2, 2)
    mu = expit(theta[1] + theta[2]*x)
    y  = rbinom(n, size=m, prob=mu)

    k = round(contam*n)
    idx = order(x, decreasing=TRUE)[1:k]
    y[idx] = 0
    x[idx] = x[idx] + delta_x

    b_mle = coef(glm(cbind(y, m-y) ~ x, family=binomial()))

    L = function(th){
      eta = th[1] + th[2]*x
      mu  = expit(eta)
      r   = y - m*mu
      c   = p * IQR(r)
      w   = exp(-pmax(0, abs(r) - c))
      cbind( w*(y - m*mu),
             w*x*(y - m*mu) )
    }
    LL = function(th){ u = colSums(L(th)); sum(u^2) }
    b_rob = try(optim(LL, par=b_mle, control=list(reltol=1e-12))$par, silent=TRUE)
    if(inherits(b_rob,"try-error")) next
    out[t,] = c(b_mle[1], b_mle[2], b_rob[1], b_rob[2])
  }
  out
}

set.seed(77)
res = mc_binom_advers(R=500, n=220, contam=0.18, delta_x=6, p=1.4)

## ==========================================================
##  Binomial robusto (IQR + exp(-(|r|-c)_+)) com contaminao
##  tipo aula (pontos baixos empurrados e rotulados 0/m)
## ==========================================================

expit = function(eta) 1/(1+exp(-eta))
set.seed(2025)

## --------------------------
## Exemplo nico (aula-style)
## --------------------------

## --------------------------
##  Monte Carlo (aula-style)
## --------------------------
mc_binom_aula = function(R=500, n=220, contam=0.10, p=1.5){
  out = matrix(NA_real_, R, 4)
  colnames(out) = c("b0_mle","b1_mle","b0_rob","b1_rob")
  theta = c(-0.5, 1.2)
  m = rep(10, n)
  for(t in 1:R){
    x = runif(n, -2, 2)
    mu = expit(theta[1] + theta[2]*x)
    y  = rbinom(n, size=m, prob=mu)
    aux = sample(which(x < 0.5), round(contam*n))
    x[aux] = x[aux] + 3
    y[aux] = ifelse(runif(length(aux)) < 0.5, 0, m[aux])
    b_mle = coef(glm(cbind(y, m-y) ~ x, family=binomial()))
    L = function(th){
      eta = th[1] + th[2]*x
      mu  = expit(eta)
      r   = y - m*mu
      c   = p * IQR(r)
      w   = exp(-pmax(0, abs(r) - c))
      cbind( w*(y - m*mu),
             w*x*(y - m*mu) )
    }
    LL = function(th){ u = colSums(L(th)); sum(u^2) }
    b_rob = try(optim(LL, par=b_mle, control=list(reltol=1e-12))$par,
                silent=TRUE)
    if(inherits(b_rob, "try-error")) next
    out[t,] = c(b_mle[1], b_mle[2], b_rob[1], b_rob[2])
  }
  out
}
